A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO MEAT DONATION.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 159, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
3 and to read as follows:
4 "§159- Further exemptions; food donations; axis deer
5 meat; pilot program. (a) There is established an axis deer
6 meat donation pilot program to allow hunters to donate meat or
7 meat products derived from axis deer to a charitable, religious,
8 or nonprofit organization for the purpose of feeding those in
9 need without regard to this chapter.
10 (b) This chapter shall not apply to the slaughtering of
11 axis deer or the preparation and transportation of the
12 carcasses, parts thereof, and meat or meat products derived from
13 axis deer at establishments conducting these operations if the
14 articles are exclusively to be donated by a hunter for the use
15 or distribution by a charitable, religious, or nonprofit
16 organization to feed needy persons pursuant to chapter 145D;
17 provided that the meat or meat products derived from axis deer
