1 shall not be combined with a meat food product regulated under
2 the Federal Meat Inspection Act, title 21 United States Code
3 section 601 et seq., or a poultry product regulated under the
4 federal Poultry Products Inspection Act, title 21 United States
5 Code section 451 et seq.; provided further that the
6 transportation of the carcasses, parts thereof, and meat or meat
7 products derived from axis deer shall be limited to moving the
8 carcasses, parts thereof, and meat or meat products derived from
9 axis deer to and from the premises where the hunter killed the
10 axis deer; the processing establishment; and the charitable,
11 religious, or nonprofit organization feeding needy persons.
12 (c) A hunter shall successfully complete a training and
13 certification program established by the department of
14 agriculture and biosecurity, in consultation with the department
15 of health, regarding safe field dressing, disease
16 identification, and proper handling of the carcasses, parts
17 thereof, and meat or meat products derived from axis deer prior
18 to donating meat or meat products derived from axis deer
19 pursuant to this section.
20 (d) The axis deer meat donation pilot program established
21 pursuant to this section shall be operative on an island with a
