2 hundred thousand; provided that if a recognized outbreak of a
3 known disease, as determined by the department of agriculture
4 and biosecurity, exists in the pilot program location, the pilot
5 program shall not continue until the outbreak is resolved, as
6 determined by the department.
7 (e) For the purposes of this section, "axis deer" means
8 the species scientifically known as Axis axis."
9 SECTION 2. Section 145D-5, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
10 amended to read as follows:
11 "§145D-5 Reserving the State's authority to regulate,
12 inspect, or ban the use of donated food. [Ne-thing in]
